3:59:58 AM [express] POST /api/mealplan 200 in 48179ms :: {"week_summary":"20-year-old moderately active male with Vata-dominant constitution aiming for weight management, no medical issues or restrictions, prefers Indian cuisine with up to 1 hour for cooking.","hydration":"Aim for about 2.5â€“3 liters of fluids daily, favoring warm water or herbal infusions; keep a 1-liter bottle near your study/work area and finish it by lunch and refill once more by evening.","weekly_strategy":"Meals emphasize warm, lightly oily, and grounding foods to balance Vata while keeping total intake around your maintenance calories for steady weight management. Each day combines complex carbs (millets, rice, oats), adequate protein (dal, dairy, legumes), and healthy fats (ghee, nuts, seeds) with Vata-pacifying spices like ginger, cumin, and fennel. Portions are designed to keep you satisfied without heaviness, supporting stable energy and digestion.","clinician_note":"","days":[{"day":1,"day_name":"Monday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Masala Vegetable Oats Upma","ingredients":["rolled oats","ghee","mustard seeds","cumin seeds","hing","curry leaves","grated carrot","chopped beans","green peas","ginger","turmeric","salt","water","fresh coriander"],"portion":"1 medium bowl ~300g","macros":{"protein":"11g","carbs":"48g","fat":"10g","calories":"340 kcal"},"why":"Warm, soft oats with ghee and mild spices ground Vata and provide steady energy for weight maintenance without heaviness.","substitutions":["Use rolled barley instead of oats","Replace ghee with cold-pressed sesame oil"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Stewed Apple with Cinnamon and Raisins","ingredients":["apple","water","cinnamon powder","raisins","small piece of jaggery (optional)"],"portion":"1 small bowl ~180g","macros":{"protein":"1g","carbs":"32g","fat":"0g","calories":"135 kcal"},"why":"Stewed warm apple with cinnamon is gentle on Vata digestion and curbs sweet cravings in a light, sattvic way.","substitutions":["Use pear instead of apple","Swap raisins with chopped dates"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Moong Dal Khichdi with Ghee Tadka","ingredients":["split yellow moong dal","white rice","ghee","cumin seeds","hing","turmeric","grated ginger","salt","carrot","bottle gourd","water","fresh coriander"],"portion":"1.5 bowls ~400g","macros":{"protein":"18g","carbs":"70g","fat":"12g","calories":"480 kcal"},"why":"Soft, soupy khichdi with ghee is classic for pacifying Vata, providing complete protein and easy-to-digest carbs for stable weight.","substitutions":["Use little millet instead of rice","Replace bottle gourd with pumpkin"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Roasted Jeera Buttermilk (Chaas) with Bhuna Chana","ingredients":["low-fat curd","water","roasted cumin powder","black salt","fresh coriander","roasted chana (whole)","ginger (optional)"],"portion":"1 glass chaas ~200ml + 20g roasted chana","macros":{"protein":"6g","carbs":"10g","fat":"3g","calories":"90 kcal"},"why":"Lightly spiced buttermilk calms Vata and supports digestion, while roasted chana adds a bit of protein and crunch without excess calories.","substitutions":["Use plain salted lassi instead of chaas in cooler weather","Swap roasted chana with a small handful of peanuts if tolerated"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Phulka, Masoor Dal Tadka and Jeera Pumpkin Sabzi","ingredients":["whole wheat flour","water","salt","masoor dal","ghee","cumin seeds","garlic","turmeric","tomato","pumpkin","mustard seeds","curry leaves","green chilli (small, optional)","coriander"],"portion":"2 phulkas (~80g) + 1 bowl dal (~200g) + 1 small bowl sabzi (~120g)","macros":{"protein":"22g","carbs":"75g","fat":"14g","calories":"540 kcal"},"why":"Warm dal, soft roti and mildly spiced pumpkin provide grounding, Vata-calming nourishment at night with good protein for muscle maintenance.","substitutions":["Use jowar rotis instead of wheat phulkas","Replace pumpkin with bottle gourd sabzi"]}}},{"day":2,"day_name":"Tuesday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Jowar Vegetable Cheela with Coriander Chutney","ingredients":["jowar flour","besan (small amount for binding)","water","salt","grated carrot","finely chopped onion","coriander leaves","cumin seeds","turmeric","ghee or oil for shallow frying","coriander","mint","lemon juice","green chilli","ginger"],"portion":"3 medium cheelas ~250g + 2 tbsp chutney","macros":{"protein":"12g","carbs":"50g","fat":"10g","calories":"360 kcal"},"why":"Warm jowar cheelas with mild spices are grounding yet light, supporting Vata balance and providing slow-release energy.","substitutions":["Use bajra flour instead of jowar","Replace chutney with a small bowl of curd if preferred"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Papaya with Lime and Roasted Fennel","ingredients":["ripe papaya","lime juice","roasted fennel seeds"],"portion":"1 cup papaya cubes ~150g","macros":{"protein":"1g","carbs":"16g","fat":"0g","calories":"65 kcal"},"why":"Ripe papaya is sweet, soft and easy to digest, ideal for Vata, while fennel and lime gently kindle digestion.","substitutions":["Use ripe guava (peeled and deseeded) instead of papaya","Swap fennel with a pinch of roasted cumin powder"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Jeera Rice with Toor Dal Fry and Beet-Carrot Stir Fry","ingredients":["basmati rice","ghee","cumin seeds","toor dal","onion","tomato","garlic","turmeric","mustard seeds","curry leaves","beetroot","carrot","salt","coriander"],"portion":"1.5 bowls jeera rice (~250g cooked) + 1 bowl dal (~200g) + 1 small bowl sabzi (~120g)","macros":{"protein":"20g","carbs":"85g","fat":"15g","calories":"600 kcal"},"why":"Jeera rice and toor dal provide a comforting, Vata-friendly combo with good protein, while beet-carrot add grounding sweetness and micronutrients.","substitutions":["Use barley instead of rice for more fiber","Replace beet-carrot with okra stir fry"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Warm Lemon-Ginger Water with Handful of Mixed Nuts","ingredients":["warm water","lemon juice","sliced ginger","almonds","walnuts","cashews"],"portion":"1 mug ~200ml + 15g mixed nuts (~10â€“12 pieces)","macros":{"protein":"4g","carbs":"6g","fat":"9g","calories":"110 kcal"},"why":"Warm lemon-ginger water supports Agni without aggravating Vata, and a small portion of nuts offers healthy fats and satiety.","substitutions":["Use tulsi tea instead of lemon-ginger water","Swap mixed nuts with just soaked almonds"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Quinoa Khichdi with Vegetables and Curry Leaves","ingredients":["quinoa","split moong dal","ghee","cumin seeds","mustard seeds","curry leaves","hing","turmeric","ginger","bottle gourd","carrot","salt","water","coriander"],"portion":"1 large bowl ~350g","macros":{"protein":"17g","carbs":"55g","fat":"10g","calories":"420 kcal"},"why":"Quinoa-moong khichdi is light yet protein-rich, with warm spices and ghee to stabilize Vata and support overnight recovery.","substitutions":["Use brown rice instead of quinoa","Replace bottle gourd with pumpkin or zucchini"]}}},{"day":3,"day_name":"Wednesday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Soft Idli with Sambar (Vata-Friendly) and Coconut-Coriander Chutney","ingredients":["idli batter (rice and urad dal fermented)","oil for greasing","toor dal","drumstick pieces","carrot","pumpkin","tomato","sambar powder (mild)","tamarind pulp (small amount)","mustard seeds","curry leaves","hing","coconut","coriander","green chilli (small)","salt"],"portion":"3 medium idlis (~180g) + 1 bowl sambar (~150g) + 2 tbsp chutney","macros":{"protein":"14g","carbs":"60g","fat":"8g","calories":"380 kcal"},"why":"Soft, warm idlis with vegetable sambar are easy to digest and grounding for Vata while providing balanced carbs and protein.","substitutions":["Use ragi idli instead of regular idli","Replace coconut chutney with tomato-coriander chutney if you prefer lighter fat"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Pomegranate and Orange Bowl","ingredients":["pomegranate arils","orange segments","black salt","roasted cumin powder"],"portion":"1 small bowl ~150g","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"30g","fat":"0g","calories":"120 kcal"},"why":"Juicy, sweet-sour fruits hydrate and nourish Vata without heaviness, and cumin helps prevent gas.","substitutions":["Use sweet lime instead of orange","Swap pomegranate with pineapple pieces if in season"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Bajra Roti with Moong-Methi Dal and Okra Stir Fry","ingredients":["bajra flour","warm water","salt","split moong dal","fresh methi leaves","ghee","cumin seeds","garlic","turmeric","tomato","okra","onion","mustard seeds","curry leaves","coriander"],"portion":"2 bajra rotis (~90g) + 1 bowl dal (~200g) + 1 small bowl okra (~120g)","macros":{"protein":"20g","carbs":"70g","fat":"14g","calories":"540 kcal"},"why":"Bajra and moong-methi dal provide warming, grounding nourishment for Vata with good protein and fiber, while okra adds mucilaginous softness for the gut.","substitutions":["Use jowar roti instead of bajra if digestion is sensitive","Replace okra with a simple carrot-beans stir fry"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Spiced Masala Milk (Vata-Calming)","ingredients":["cow's milk or toned milk","water (to dilute slightly)","cardamom powder","turmeric","nutmeg (pinch)","black pepper (pinch)","small piece jaggery or honey (added warm, not hot)"],"portion":"1 cup ~200ml","macros":{"protein":"7g","carbs":"12g","fat":"6g","calories":"130 kcal"},"why":"Warm spiced milk with cardamom and nutmeg is classic for calming Vata nerves and provides protein and fat for satiety.","substitutions":["Use almond milk if avoiding dairy","Skip jaggery and use stevia if you want to reduce sugar"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Soft Rice, Palak Chana Dal and Carrot-Beans Poriyal","ingredients":["white rice","chana dal","spinach (palak)","ghee","cumin seeds","garlic","turmeric","onion","carrot","green beans","mustard seeds","curry leaves","grated coconut (optional)","salt"],"portion":"1.5 bowls rice (~250g cooked) + 1 bowl dal (~200g) + 1 small bowl poriyal (~120g)","macros":{"protein":"19g","carbs":"80g","fat":"13g","calories":"560 kcal"},"why":"Soft rice with palak chana dal offers a comforting, protein-rich meal that is easy on Vata digestion while poriyal adds gentle fiber.","substitutions":["Use moong dal instead of chana dal if you feel heavy","Replace poriyal with a simple pumpkin sabzi"]}}},{"day":4,"day_name":"Thursday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Sweet Potato Poha with Peanuts and Curry Leaves","ingredients":["thick poha (flattened rice)","boiled sweet potato cubes","onion","green chilli (small)","curry leaves","mustard seeds","turmeric","peanuts","ghee or oil","lemon juice","coriander","salt"],"portion":"1 medium plate ~280g","macros":{"protein":"8g","carbs":"55g","fat":"11g","calories":"380 kcal"},"why":"Soft, warm poha with sweet potato and peanuts is grounding and slightly sweet, ideal for Vata while keeping you full through the morning.","substitutions":["Use boiled potato instead of sweet potato occasionally","Replace peanuts with cashews if preferred"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Amla-Ginger Honey Shot with Warm Water","ingredients":["amla juice (fresh or bottled, unsweetened)","grated ginger","honey","warm water"],"portion":"1 small glass ~100ml + 100ml warm water","macros":{"protein":"0g","carbs":"8g","fat":"0g","calories":"30 kcal"},"why":"Amla and ginger support immunity and digestion; taken diluted and warm, it gently stimulates Agni without disturbing Vata.","substitutions":["Use lemon juice instead of amla if unavailable","Skip honey if you prefer unsweetened"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Barley Vegetable Pulao with Curd","ingredients":["pearled barley","ghee","cumin seeds","bay leaf","clove","carrot","beans","peas","onion","ginger-garlic paste","turmeric","garam masala (small pinch)","salt","curd"],"portion":"1.5 bowls pulao (~300g) + 1/2 cup curd (~100g)","macros":{"protein":"15g","carbs":"80g","fat":"12g","calories":"520 kcal"},"why":"Barley provides slow-digesting carbs and fiber for weight management, while ghee and warm spices keep it Vata-friendly and curd adds protein.","substitutions":["Use brown rice instead of barley if you feel too dry","Replace curd with raita including cucumber and coriander"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Guava Chaat with Black Pepper and Rock Salt","ingredients":["ripe guava (peeled and deseeded if needed)","black pepper","rock salt","lemon juice"],"portion":"1 small bowl ~150g","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"18g","fat":"1g","calories":"80 kcal"},"why":"Guava offers vitamin C and fiber; seasoning with pepper and rock salt makes it more digestible for Vata.","substitutions":["Use apple instead of guava","Swap lemon juice with orange juice splash"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Lemon Rice with Peanuts and Simple Moong Dal Soup","ingredients":["cooked white rice","ghee or sesame oil","mustard seeds","curry leaves","turmeric","green chilli (small)","peanuts","lemon juice","split yellow moong dal","cumin seeds","hing","ginger","salt","coriander"],"portion":"1 medium plate lemon rice (~250g) + 1 bowl thin moong soup (~180g)","macros":{"protein":"16g","carbs":"75g","fat":"14g","calories":"540 kcal"},"why":"Lemon rice is light yet satisfying, and pairing with thin moong soup adds protein and warmth to keep Vata grounded at night.","substitutions":["Use brown rice instead of white rice","Replace peanuts with cashews if digestion is sensitive"]}}},{"day":5,"day_name":"Friday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Ragi Porridge with Jaggery and Nuts","ingredients":["ragi flour","water","milk","jaggery","cardamom powder","ghee (small amount)","chopped almonds","cashews"],"portion":"1 bowl ~300g","macros":{"protein":"11g","carbs":"55g","fat":"10g","calories":"380 kcal"},"why":"Warm, slightly sweet ragi porridge is nourishing and grounding for Vata, with calcium and fiber to support long-lasting satiety.","substitutions":["Use oats instead of ragi if you prefer milder taste","Replace jaggery with mashed banana for sweetness"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Carrot and Cucumber Sticks with Lemon-Cumin Sprinkle","ingredients":["carrot","cucumber (peeled)","lemon juice","roasted cumin powder","salt"],"portion":"1 plate ~150g","macros":{"protein":"2g","carbs":"10g","fat":"0g","calories":"45 kcal"},"why":"Raw veggies in small quantity with warming cumin and lemon provide crunch and hydration without overloading Vata.","substitutions":["Use lightly steamed carrot if raw is hard to digest","Swap cucumber with blanched beans sticks"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Plain Parboiled Rice, Sambar with Drumsticks and Cabbage Thoran","ingredients":["parboiled rice","toor dal","drumsticks","carrot","pumpkin","tomato","sambar powder (mild)","tamarind (small amount)","mustard seeds","curry leaves","hing","oil or ghee","cabbage","grated coconut","green chilli","salt"],"portion":"1.5 bowls rice (~250g cooked) + 1 bowl sambar (~200g) + 1 small bowl thoran (~120g)","macros":{"protein":"18g","carbs":"82g","fat":"13g","calories":"560 kcal"},"why":"Rice with vegetable-rich sambar is light yet filling, and cabbage thoran adds fiber and healthy fats, all cooked soft to suit Vata.","substitutions":["Use moong dal instead of toor dal for lighter sambar","Replace cabbage with beans or carrot thoran"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Tulsi-Ginger Herbal Tea with 2 Khakhras","ingredients":["water","fresh tulsi leaves or dried tulsi","ginger slices","cardamom (optional)","plain whole wheat khakhra"],"portion":"1 cup tea ~200ml + 2 small khakhras (~30g)","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"18g","fat":"3g","calories":"110 kcal"},"why":"Warm tulsi-ginger tea calms Vata and supports immunity, while light khakhra gives a controlled crunch to manage hunger.","substitutions":["Use jeera tea instead of tulsi-ginger","Swap khakhra with 2 small whole wheat biscuits"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Stuffed Lauki (Bottle Gourd) Paratha with Curd","ingredients":["whole wheat flour","grated bottle gourd (squeezed lightly)","coriander","green chilli (small)","cumin seeds","turmeric","salt","ghee or oil for roasting","curd"],"portion":"2 medium parathas (~180g) + 1/2 cup curd (~100g)","macros":{"protein":"14g","carbs":"60g","fat":"14g","calories":"480 kcal"},"why":"Soft, warm lauki parathas with curd are soothing and grounding for Vata, providing a balanced mix of carbs, protein and fat for dinner.","substitutions":["Use methi instead of lauki for stuffing","Replace curd with thin kadhi if you prefer a warm side"]}}},{"day":6,"day_name":"Saturday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Vegetable Semolina (Rava) Upma with Curry Leaves","ingredients":["semolina (rava)","ghee or oil","mustard seeds","urad dal (small amount)","chana dal (small amount)","curry leaves","ginger","onion","carrot","peas","beans","water","salt","lemon juice","coriander"],"portion":"1 medium bowl ~280g","macros":{"protein":"9g","carbs":"55g","fat":"10g","calories":"370 kcal"},"why":"Warm, soft upma with vegetables and ghee is ideal for pacifying Vata and provides steady energy for an active day.","substitutions":["Use broken wheat (dalia) instead of semolina","Replace peas with corn if preferred"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Banana with Peanut Butter","ingredients":["medium banana","natural peanut butter (unsweetened)"],"portion":"1 banana (~100g) + 1 tbsp peanut butter (~15g)","macros":{"protein":"4g","carbs":"30g","fat":"7g","calories":"200 kcal"},"why":"Bananaâ€™s sweet, heavy quality grounds Vata, and peanut butter adds protein and healthy fat to keep you full.","substitutions":["Use almond butter instead of peanut butter","Swap banana with 2 small dates if you want a lighter option"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Rajma Masala with Steamed Rice and Simple Salad","ingredients":["rajma (kidney beans, soaked and boiled)","onion","tomato","ginger-garlic paste","oil or ghee","cumin seeds","turmeric","coriander powder","garam masala (small amount)","salt","white rice","carrot","cucumber (peeled)","lemon juice"],"portion":"1.5 bowls rice (~250g cooked) + 1 bowl rajma (~200g) + small salad (~80g)","macros":{"protein":"20g","carbs":"90g","fat":"12g","calories":"600 kcal"},"why":"Rajma-chawal is hearty and grounding, suitable for Vata when cooked soft and spiced well, and offers good plant protein for muscle support.","substitutions":["Use brown rice instead of white rice","Replace rajma with chole if you prefer chickpeas"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Roasted Makhana with Turmeric and Pepper","ingredients":["makhana (fox nuts)","ghee","turmeric","black pepper","salt"],"portion":"1 small bowl ~20g","macros":{"protein":"3g","carbs":"12g","fat":"4g","calories":"100 kcal"},"why":"Lightly roasted makhana in ghee is a classic Vata snackâ€”light yet grounding, with spices to aid digestion.","substitutions":["Use roasted chana instead of makhana","Swap ghee with coconut oil for a different flavor"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Vegetable Dalia Khichdi with Ghee","ingredients":["broken wheat (dalia)","split moong dal","ghee","cumin seeds","hing","turmeric","ginger","bottle gourd","carrot","peas","water","salt","coriander"],"portion":"1 large bowl ~350g","macros":{"protein":"16g","carbs":"60g","fat":"9g","calories":"420 kcal"},"why":"Soft dalia-moong khichdi is very Vata-friendly, providing complex carbs and protein in a light, easily digestible form for dinner.","substitutions":["Use oats instead of dalia","Replace bottle gourd with pumpkin"]}}},{"day":7,"day_name":"Sunday","meals":{"breakfast":{"dish_name":"Paneer Bhurji with Multigrain Toast","ingredients":["paneer (crumbled)","onion","tomato","capsicum (small amount)","ghee or oil","cumin seeds","turmeric","coriander powder","green chilli (small, optional)","salt","coriander leaves","multigrain bread slices"],"portion":"1 bowl paneer bhurji (~150g) + 2 slices toast (~60g)","macros":{"protein":"20g","carbs":"35g","fat":"18g","calories":"420 kcal"},"why":"Warm, spiced paneer provides high-quality protein and fat to ground Vata, and multigrain toast adds complex carbs for energy.","substitutions":["Use tofu instead of paneer","Replace toast with 2 small phulkas"]},"morning_snack":{"dish_name":"Pineapple-Coriander Cooler (Lightly Spiced)","ingredients":["pineapple pieces","coriander leaves","black salt","roasted cumin powder","water"],"portion":"1 glass ~200ml","macros":{"protein":"1g","carbs":"22g","fat":"0g","calories":"90 kcal"},"why":"Pineapple with coriander and cumin is refreshing yet digestive, taken at room temperature to avoid aggravating Vata.","substitutions":["Use orange instead of pineapple","Skip coriander if you dislike the flavor"]},"lunch":{"dish_name":"Chicken Curry (Light Home-Style) with Rice and Salad","ingredients":["chicken (bone-in or boneless, skinless)","onion","tomato","ginger-garlic paste","oil or ghee","cumin seeds","turmeric","coriander powder","garam masala (small amount)","curd (for marination)","salt","white rice","cucumber (peeled)","carrot","lemon juice"],"portion":"1.5 bowls rice (~250g cooked) + 1 medium bowl chicken curry (~180g) + small salad (~80g)","macros":{"protein":"28g","carbs":"80g","fat":"16g","calories":"640 kcal"},"why":"Soft, mildly spiced chicken curry offers high-quality protein for muscle maintenance, and rice keeps it grounding and Vata-friendly.","substitutions":["Use fish curry instead of chicken","Replace rice with 2â€“3 phulkas if you prefer wheat"]},"evening_snack":{"dish_name":"Spiced Sproutless Chaat with Boiled Chana","ingredients":["boiled black chana or kabuli chana","onion (small amount)","tomato","coriander","lemon juice","roasted cumin powder","black salt","chopped green chilli (optional)"],"portion":"1 small bowl ~120g","macros":{"protein":"7g","carbs":"20g","fat":"1g","calories":"120 kcal"},"why":"Boiled chana chaat gives a protein-rich, tangy snack without raw sprouts, making it more digestible for Vata.","substitutions":["Use boiled moong instead of chana","Add a spoon of curd to make it creamier and more Vata-calming"]},"dinner":{"dish_name":"Jeera Rice with Kadhi and Simple Aloo-Jeera","ingredients":["basmati rice","ghee","cumin seeds","curd","besan","water","turmeric","ginger","green chilli (small)","mustard seeds","curry leaves","hing","boiled potatoes","cumin seeds","coriander","salt"],"portion":"1.5 bowls jeera rice (~250g cooked) + 1 bowl kadhi (~200g) + small portion aloo-jeera (~100g)","macros":{"protein":"15g","carbs":"85g","fat":"18g","calories":"620 kcal"},"why":"Warm kadhi-rice with soft aloo-jeera is comforting and grounding, ideal for calming Vata on a relaxed Sunday evening.","substitutions":["Use khichdi instead of jeera rice if digestion feels weak","Replace aloo-jeera with lauki sabzi for a lighter option"]}}}]}
